<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>The Teapot Dome scandal during the Harding administration involved:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Secret leasing of naval oil reserves for bribes</option>
            <option letter="b">Illegal alcohol distribution during Prohibition</option>
            <option letter="c">Stock market manipulation</option>
            <option letter="d">Voter fraud in the 1920 election</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>The Teapot Dome scandal was a bribery scandal where Secretary of the Interior Albert Fall secretly leased naval oil reserves in Wyoming (Teapot Dome) and California to private oil companies in exchange for bribes. This became the most notorious scandal of the Harding administration and resulted in Fall's imprisonment, marking the first time a U.S. cabinet member was sent to prison.</explanation>
    </question>
